005package edu.wpi.first.networktables;
006
007/** NetworkTables log message. */
008@SuppressWarnings("MemberName")
009public final class LogMessage {
010  /** Logging levels. */
011  public static final int kCritical = 50;
012
013  public static final int kError = 40;
014  public static final int kWarning = 30;
015  public static final int kInfo = 20;
016  public static final int kDebug = 10;
017  public static final int kDebug1 = 9;
018  public static final int kDebug2 = 8;
019  public static final int kDebug3 = 7;
020  public static final int kDebug4 = 6;
021
022  /** The logger that generated the message. */
023  public final int logger;
024
025  /** Log level of the message. */
026  public final int level;
027
028  /** The filename of the source file that generated the message. */
029  public final String filename;
030
031  /** The line number in the source file that generated the message. */
032  public final int line;
033
034  /** The message. */
035  public final String message;
036
037  /**
038   * Constructor. This should generally only be used internally to NetworkTables.
039   *
040   * @param inst Instance
041   * @param logger Logger
042   * @param level Log level
043   * @param filename Filename
044   * @param line Line number
045   * @param message Message
046   */
047  public LogMessage(
048      NetworkTableInstance inst, int logger, int level, String filename, int line, String message) {
049    this.m_inst = inst;
050    this.logger = logger;
051    this.level = level;
052    this.filename = filename;
053    this.line = line;
054    this.message = message;
055  }
056
057  private final NetworkTableInstance m_inst;
058
059  NetworkTableInstance getInstance() {
060    return m_inst;
061  }
062}
